# Card Sorting

<catsoop-section>Introduction</catsoop-section>

If you have cards with numbers. But they are not in consecutive numbers. You need to arrange them in a consecutive system then how will you do it? Take them one by one and arrange them by their order. This? Don't you think it will be a very time consuming manner? Then what to do? Let's do it. Do you know computers use binary language for processing? Same thing we will do here.

<catsoop-section>Materials Required</catsoop-section>

- Cards with punching by hole and slit according to their numbers in binary system
- Stick

