<catsoop-section>Instructions</catsoop-section>

1. First arrange all the cards with the same faces on one side and upright.

2. Now keep all the holes aligned with other cards.

3. Now take a stick and insert it in the first hole from right side. Shake them carefully and collect those cards which are not hanging in a stick. Collect these cards without changing their order and put these cards back to the hanging cards and remove the stick.

4. Insert the stick in the second hole from the right side.

5. Repeat this process until the stick passes from all the holes respectively.

6. Now see your cards. It will be arranged in order.

<catsoop-section>What's Happening</catsoop-section>

Here we made holes as binary numbers. At 1 we made slits and at 0 we made holes. So cards will fall down from slits and will hang at holes. See the binary patterns:

$$\begin{array}{|c|c||c|c||c|c|}
\hline
\textbf{Number} & \textbf{Binary} & \textbf{Number} & \textbf{Binary} & \textbf{Number} & \textbf{Binary} \\
\hline
1 & 0001 & 6 & 0110 & 11 & 1011 \\
\hline
2 & 0010 & 7 & 0111 & 12 & 1100 \\
\hline
3 & 0011 & 8 & 1000 & 13 & 1101 \\
\hline
4 & 0100 & 9 & 1001 & 14 & 1110 \\
\hline
5 & 0101 & 10 & 1010 & 15 & 1111 \\
\hline
\end{array}$$

You can see the patterns. In the first card the right most hole has slit and remaining are holes. In second card the second hole from right has slit and others are holes.

While inserting stick in the first right most hole, the cards which have slit will fall down which are 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11, ... (odd numbers). These cards go backwards.

On the second round the cards which have slit on the second hole from right will fall down and go backward. Means 2, 3, 6, 7, 10, 11, ...

Continuing this process without changing their order while collecting slipping cards through slits, the cards will automatically be arranged in ascending order.

